24/01/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu and the World Bank's Country Manager for Albania, Nadir Mohammed, met on Tuesday (January 23rd) to discuss the ongoing energy crisis in the country. Mohamed reportedly suggested increased electricity imports, as well as acceleration of long-term initiatives on behalf of Albania's energy sector. 
Separately Tuesday, the state power utility KESH announced that the company already had boosted electricity imports and is working to reduce the duration of daily power cuts to about three hours a day. (Albanian News - 24/01/07; Albanian President website - 23/01/07)
